    (24,3,'Blue River Confluence','weaver','2008-04-13',2.44,'','3','sucky... just too much water coming down the mckenzie, making the convergence not a defined line.',0,'2019-09-10 12:03:55 -0400', '2019-09-10 12:03:55 -0400'),
    (1,3,'Squirt Ranch','weaver','2007-07-16',900,'','5','getting really low... still ok, but takes a lot of work...',0,'2019-09-10 12:03:55 -0400', '2019-09-10 12:03:55 -0400'),
    (27,3,'Champange Jam','weaver','2007-01-01',730,'','3','not so good at this level…. I think last summer it was higher water, like perhaps 1000-1500,…and with this higher flow, you can attain all the way up past the Watch Tower and get to the Jam.',0,'2019-09-10 12:03:55 -0400', '2019-09-10 12:03:55 -0400'),
    (60,3,'Big Eddy','weaver','2008-05-17',8000,'','5','Joel and i got in here to do some probing. We stayed mostly in the river right big eddy proper.. joel got a couple head under moves, but the line was kinda mushy. There where HUGE logs and other debrie floating around with us... semi sketch.. \r\n\r\nI paddled far up stream to take a look at the huge whirlpool beast on river left.. ALOT of power up there. Just skirted the edge of it and thats all i wanted.. probably would give up dynamic/oblivian charcs that would throw you around like a leaf in the wind. not too sweet...scarey actually. \r\n\r\nAlso paddled across to the eddy line on river left below the beast, where the rock wall ends, but it wasnt ideal either and gave nothing up.  Pretty interesting arena to paddle around in, but not a place for safe quality mysteries...  ',0,'2019-09-10 12:03:55 -0400', '2019-09-10 12:03:55 -0400'),
    (25,3,'Watch Tower','weaver','2008-01-17',555,'','5','kinda sucked...',0,'2019-09-10 12:03:55 -0400', '2019-09-10 12:03:55 -0400'),
